1 cell phones and personal electronic devices while on the campus of a
2 public school district from bell to bell for three (3) school years,
3 beginning with the 2025-2026 school year.
4 B. Grants awarded pursuant to this section shall be used during
5 the 2025-2026 school year to purchase devices or equipment in which
6 students enrolled in a grant recipient school district can store
7 their cell phones and personal electronic devices during the school
8 day. In conjunction with the Office of Management and Enterprise
9 Services, the Office of Educational Quality and Accountability may
10 negotiate and enter into a contract with a vendor to offer a state
11 rate price to grant recipient school districts; provided, however, a
12 grant recipient school district shall not be required to use a
13 vendor contracted by the Office of Educational Quality and
14 Accountability.
15 C. Grant recipient school districts shall electronically submit
16 a report to the Office of Educational Quality and Accountability
17 detailing how grant funds were used.
18 D. The Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability
19 shall be authorized to promulgate rules in order to effectuate the
20 provisions of this section.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
22 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
23 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
